# Load the combined dataset
all_accidents = pd.read_csv('all_accidents.csv')

all_accidents['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(all_accidents['Date'], errors='coerce')

# Ensure Fatality column is numeric
all_accidents['Fatality'] = pd.to_numeric(all_accidents['Fatality'], errors='coerce')

### 1. Count of Accidents in Each Dataset
accident_counts = all_accidents['Type'].value_counts()
print("Accident Counts:")
print(accident_counts)

fatalities_stats = all_accidents.groupby('Type')['Fatality'].agg(['sum', 'mean'])

In [23]:
# Ensure 'Date' is datetime and extract year
all_accidents['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(all_accidents['Date'], errors='coerce')
all_accidents['Year'] = all_accidents['Date'].dt.year

# Group by year and count accidents
yearly_trend = all_accidents.groupby('Year').size()

# Identify peak years
peak_years = yearly_trend[yearly_trend == yearly_trend.max()]
print(f"Peak Years with Most Accidents:\n{peak_years}")

# Visualization: Yearly trend of accidents
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.lineplot(x=yearly_trend.index, y=yearly_trend.values, marker='o', color='blue')
plt.title("Yearly Trend of Accidents")
plt.xlabel("Year")
plt.ylabel("Number of Accidents")
plt.axvline(x=peak_years.index[0], color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Peak Year: {peak_years.index[0]}")
plt.grid()
plt.legend()
plt.show()

In [15]:
# Group by 'Operator' and 'Type' to get counts
operator_counts_by_type = all_accidents.groupby(['Type', 'Operator']).size().reset_index(name='Count')

# Overall counts for all types
operator_counts_overall = all_accidents.groupby('Operator').size().reset_index(name='Count')

### 1. Visualize Accidents by Operator for Each Type
types = all_accidents['Type'].unique()

for dataset_type in types:
    # Filter data for each type
    type_data = operator_counts_by_type[operator_counts_by_type['Type'] == dataset_type]
    # Sort by count
    type_data = type_data.sort_values(by='Count', ascending=False)
    
    # Visualization
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.bar(type_data['Operator'], type_data['Count'], color='skyblue')
    plt.title(f"Accidents by Operator ({dataset_type.capitalize()})")
    plt.xlabel("Operator")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Accidents")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

In [20]:
### 2. Visualization: Accidents by Operator and Type of Aircraft for Each Dataset Type
types = all_accidents['Type'].unique()

for dataset_type in types:
    # Filter data for each type
    type_data = grouped_data[grouped_data['Type'] == dataset_type]
    type_data = type_data.sort_values(by='Count', ascending=False)

    # Visualization
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    for operator in type_data['Operator'].unique()[:5]:  # Limit to top 5 operators for readability
        operator_data = type_data[type_data['Operator'] == operator]
        plt.bar(operator_data['Type of Aircraft'], operator_data['Count'], label=operator)
    
    plt.title(f"Accidents by Operator and Aircraft Type ({dataset_type.capitalize()})")
    plt.xlabel("Type of Aircraft")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Accidents")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.legend(title="Operator", loc='upper right')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

### 3. Visualization: Overall Accidents by Operator and Aircraft Type (All Types Combined)
# Group by 'Operator' and 'Type of Aircraft' for overall visualization
overall_data = all_accidents.groupby(['Operator', 'Type of Aircraft']).size().reset_index(name='Count')
overall_data = overall_data.sort_values(by='Count', ascending=False)

# Limit to top 10 operators for readability
top_operators = overall_data['Operator'].value_counts().index[:10]

plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
for operator in top_operators:
    operator_data = overall_data[overall_data['Operator'] == operator]
    plt.bar(operator_data['Type of Aircraft'], operator_data['Count'], label=operator)

plt.title("Overall Accidents by Operator and Aircraft Type (All Types Combined)")
plt.xlabel("Type of Aircraft")
plt.ylabel("Number of Accidents")
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.legend(title="Operator", loc='upper right')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
